 historical, ideological, and theoretical contexts to explore various manifestations of Athenian masculinity as well as the rhetoric that both articulated and questioned it. Roisman focuses on topics such as the nexus between manhood and age; on Athenian men in their roles as family members, friends, and lovers; on the concept of masculine shame; on relations between social and economic status and manhood; on manhood in the military and politics; on the manly virtue of self-control; and on what men feared.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aMasculinityzGreecezAthensxHistoryyClassical age. 0aMasculinityzGreecezAthensxHistoryyclassical age. 0aRhetoric, Ancient. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh  aancient athens.  aancient greece.  aancient world.  aathenian masculinity.  aathens.  aattic.  ademos.  adomesticity.  aeconomic status.  aeros.  afathers and sons.  afear.  agender studies.  agender.  agreed.  agreek men.  ahead of household.  ahellenism.  ahomosexuality.  ahonor.  ahusband.  akharis.  akinship.  akurios.  amanhood.  amanliness.  amanly values.  amanly virtue.  amarriage.  amasculine shame.  amasculinity.  amens studies.  amilitary.  anonfiction.  apeace.  apity.  apleasure.  apolitics.  apride.  arhetoric.  aself control.  asexuality.  ashame.  asocial history.  ason.  astatus.  aviolence.  awar.  awealth.  ayouth.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052024192340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093113840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520931138423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520931138/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package